after spotting the sighting i called a friend to come check them out but he could see them anymore from where he was at that moment (about a mile away).

it, wondering what it could be i could only see the underbelly of this craft. the object was round emanating a white light with a blueish tint. i noticed a dark shaded center spot. around this spot was a dark shaded ring, about the same shade as the spot. the circumference was also the same dark shade but it seem to have a pattern but not sure. these areas were not completely dark, just a shade. the light emanating from this craft formed a halo affect around it. in the halo i can see the clouds moving away from the craft(not around it)like the way fire moves. this object seem to have some obscured affect, shield or energy not sure but i was able to make it out. not sure of the size, but i estimate it was the size of a .25 cent coin if you held it just front of you as you. clouds were not very high, this object was just above the bottom layer of the clouds. i was confused as to what i saw, i tried to rationalize as to what it could be. the feeling i got from it was the feeling that i was not suppose to see it, but it got caught. then it just dissapeared before it reached the end of the cloud as i waited to see it come out. if you have any questions please call me anytime. i work graveyard i'm up through the night.

content.detailedDescription:
8:00pm, may 10, 2011, i was driving south bound on i-35 after a gas-up in kansas city when i needed to pulling into a rest stop to fix a bad map sensor in my 93 chevy van. as i was parking my van in the diagonal parking spaces facing north east of this rest stop (location is near homewood township, kansas, elevation 1,040 feet, latitude: 38-30'53'' n longitude: 095-22'44'' w.), i noticed a quarter moon setting low in the eastern horizon in a bright red color. having seen objects in the sky on previous road trips, i was prepared with two tripod mounted digital cameras (#1 cam is a jvc's gc-fm1au 1080 hd and #2 cam is a sony's hms-cm1 mp4 hd camera) ready to shoot which i had setup in the passenger compartment of the van. i quickly brought both cameras out and to the front of the van. i extended the tripods and made sure they where well seated on the concrete sidewalk and i made sure the cameras where adjusted and locked into a level plane before i began shooting photos.

the night air had a slight chill but yet the temperature was comfortable. the wind had a constant breeze from the south and the sky was quite clear with no cloud obstructions however there was a cloud formation about 40 to 50 miles south of my location. 

just after the red moon set below the horizon, i got a hair-raising-sensation in the back of my neck and rapidly snapped a few more photos with the sony hms-cm1 hd mp4 camera. i could only see the stars in the horizon at the time of the hair-raising-sensation so i did not know what i was photographing. after taking this next set of photos, i became real sleepy and decided to pack-up the tripods and take a nap in the van. i believe i sleep for four hours and then continued on my road trip.

the photographs enclosed are the four of the eight photos taken after the red moon has set below the horizon. i have used two stars in the horizon as point of reference. what the non-solid celestial object is - is unknown. the time line of photos (there were eight photos take total but these photos 8:03:06pm, 8:03:22pm, 8:03:32pm, and 8:04:12pm) show the object phasing in then out of sight then it is moving into the winds direction. i could not see this thing at the time the photos were being taken, i just had a feeling it was there.
content.summary: Non-solid celestial object

content.detailedDescription:
My wife and i were in the parking lot of a very crowded movie theater but all the way down at the very end of the lot. we had just left the new pirates of carribean movie and were walking back to out car.

when we got to the car i was walking around to open the door for my wife and we were discussing something when all of a sudden my eye caught something moving...I looked up and saw an amazing sight.

what looked at first like a fireworks piece was shooting across the sky but it was to me very close maybe only 100-300 feet above us. it was moving fast with no noise and seemed to be about 30-50 feet long and maybe only 4-6 feet wide.

this did not seem like a typical ufo type " craft " but rather more of a fireball type vessel...

it seemed to have a circular head and then brilliant blue, red and orange maybe a little yellow ish tail like rear end.

i was so amazed i mumbled " what is that " to my wife who then looked up and saw it as well. 

we both watched together for only 2-3 seconds then as if it knew we had spotted it..While still in motion it simply vanished. no smoke, no sounds nothing just gone.

we both stood their amazed and questioning each other what the heck it was.

neither of us has ever seen anything like that ever. very very amazing and cool to experience and unlike anything we've ever seen.


neither of us are artists but we came home and each independently drew best we could what we saw. we have attached.
content.summary: Outside movie parking lot a moving object caught my eye i looked up and it was moving strait, fast brilliant colors then it vanished

content.detailedDescription:
i saw a light emerge from the clouds that was stationary it lasted about 5 seconds.  it was about 45 degrees above the horizon, 25 degrees above my treeline, se direction. 
     it was about 10:45pm pacific time.  i was sitting in my back yard star gazing in rock island, wa.  the light faded in almost the exact appearance of a star except for it got brighter and brighter till it was flaring out about half of the size that the moon is. looked exactly like landing gear light on an airplane, but only one light off white, with no wing lights or flashing.  
     after it faded out in about 5 seconds, i realized there were no clouds there, that i was almost sure from which it had appeared.  no sound.  the eerie thing is that it was perfectly stationary like a star, looked like an airplane, no sound and linear fade in and out.  meteor?  what are the odds that it could come perfectly straight at me with no color variation, and for five seconds?  i wanted to think supernova at first, but very man made looking color like halogen head light.  no size just point like emission of light that kept growing.  no ability to detect approximate elevation either.  
     the yakima firing range is about 30 miles sw of here, so i was also thinking maybe some kind of military lighting beam or some energy project.  it was substantial enough to put me into shock, and make me want to log on the internet and see if anyone else saw it. or from where they might have seen it, so we could triangulate a potential altitude.  i'm mostly just confounded since i do a lot of star gazing and have never seen anything quite like it.
content.summary: I was stargazing and saw a stationary light fade in about half as bright as the moon, then back out.

it was not going fast enough to be a plane, and it did not fly in a straight line. it bobbed across the sky before fading out, or going behind a cloud.  in any case, it was gone after that.

when it was gone, i said to my friend "we just saw a ufo!". he said "really? you think so?" i said "was it an "unidentified flying object? yeah we just saw a ufo!"

we then drove out to the country side where the city lights aren't so bright and watched the sky for another couple hours, but didn't see anything else.

content.detailedDescription: Summertime, @1977, oscoda,mi. downtown at the park on lake huron. i was with my friend robbie around 10pm playing on the swings, we noticed an aircraft coming towards us, first the lights, then as the object came closer we thought it was a jet landing at wurtsmith afb. as it came closer we could see that it was not a jet, but a large black object ( size of a three bedroom house) it stopped and floated there , above the fishing pier about a 100 feet in the air. when the object stopped we noticed it made no sound. being frightened, we ran into these six foot diameter concrete pipes and watched the object from there. the oject was jet black with rotating and glowing lights ( white) pulsing. it stayed motionless for @ an hour, then all of a sudden it went up and took off extremely fast towards canada. the object was witnesed by at least three other people besides myself. the weather was clear and warm , a beautiful summer night , no moon.I was told the local police called the base to ask them if the object was theirs, they said they had nothing on radar, and when they sent two jets to investigate, the object took off so fast across the lake, it was gone within seconds.Official report said it was a weather baloon, however i was there, it was not a baloon,  it left too quickly.
content.flightPath: Hovering then path,Path with directional change
content.summary: Large black object  ( big as a small house )  hovered  a 100 feet up in the ai r  , above the fishing pier.   made no sound,, less than two miles from wurtsmith air force base,,  object was witnessed by at least  three people,, object made no sound.
